        "content": "<p>Hi,<br>\nI'm new here. I have an interest for math, but I consider myself a newbie. I have a background in electronics and computer science. I got interested in Lean after a long chain of other failed attempts to create an assistant for solving the puzzles in the book \"to mock a mockingbird and other logic puzzles\" by Raymond Smullyan. </p>\n<p>First half of the book are classical logic puzzle with liars and through tellers for example. Most of these puzzles I was able to solve.<br>\nThe second half of are puzzles with song birds, and here I hit a brick wall. I was unable to easily reason about the puzzles. Created my own notation to write down the given information, and \"proof\" steps in an attempt to be able to better reason about the puzzle. But often wondered if the steps that I took where valid. </p>\n<p>After watching Tsoding (a recreational programmer) write Noq (\"Simple expression transformer that is NOT Coq\") I wanted a similar tool for the bird puzzle problems.<br>\nStart of the video series can be found here when interested: <br>\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ra_Fk7JFMoo\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ra_Fk7JFMoo</a> </p>\n<div class=\"youtube-video message_inline_image\"><a data-id=\"Ra_Fk7JFMoo\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ra_Fk7JFMoo\"><img src=\"https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/b8353cde137b2b51a3ba87510e4ef87e96b34702/68747470733a2f2f692e7974696d672e636f6d2f76692f52615f466b374a464d6f6f2f64656661756c742e6a7067\"></a></div><p>I tried to write my own tool, without success. Recently I learned about Lean, and I wonder if it can be used as an assistant to solve these puzzles. But I have no idea how to approach this.</p>\n<p>I hope people are somewhat familiar with the book, otherwise the following will make little sense. I could make some pictures of the first puzzle to give some more context if necessary.</p>\n<p>This is the notation I came up with when I tried to write my own tool. It defines the first puzzle.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">C1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Bx</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⇒</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Cx</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">mocking</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">My</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">yy</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">fond</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">XY</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">C2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mocking</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">C1</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">C2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">?-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fond</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>An these are some older notes of the manual \"proof\" steps that I would like to be able to make.</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>k</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>g</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≡</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">mocking(M) \\equiv \\forall x: Mx = xx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">oc</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">kin</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">xx</span></span></span></span><br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≡</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">fond(A, B) \\equiv AB = B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span><br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>A</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_1 : \\forall A, B, x: \\exists C: A(Bx) = Cx </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" sty