><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall A: \\exists C: A(CC) = CC </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">CC</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">CC</span></span></span></span><br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall A: \\exists C: fond(A,CC)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">CC</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>I know that the bird puzzles are based on lambda-calculus so the examples, such as <a href=\"https://lean-lang.org/lean4/doc/examples/deBruijn.lean.html\">https://lean-lang.org/lean4/doc/examples/deBruijn.lean.html</a> might be useful.</p>\n<p>Is this something that can be done with Lean? How would one encode these kind of puzzles into Lean? Can somebody help me to get started or point me into the right direction?</p>",
